COMMENDATIONS. Commends Rosa Mae Briley Pitre on the occasion of her one
hundredth birthday.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and celebrate Rosa Mae Briley Pitre on the momentous occasion of her one
3 hundredth birthday.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Rosa Pitre for her incredible life and to
5 commend and celebrate her on the occasion of her one hundredth birthday; and
6 WHEREAS, Rosa was born on June 9, 1926, in Grand Prairie, Louisiana, to Lee and
7 Clemence Briley, and following the untimely passing of her first husband, Calvin Fontenot,
8 she was later married to Harry Pitre; and
9 WHEREAS, she is the proud and loving mother of five children: David Paul
10 Fontenot, Arlene Pitre Coreil, Janice Pitre Colligan, Peggy Pitre Tate, and John Pitre; and
11 WHEREAS, Rosa was a devoted housewife and worked as a skilled seamstress,
12 reliable telephone operator, and a respected department manager for West Bros.; and
13 WHEREAS, she is a woman of deep and abiding faith, a devout Catholic and a
14 faithful member of Sacred Heart Church in Ville Platte, Louisiana, who prays the Rosary on
15 a daily basis and receives Holy Communion every week; and
16 WHEREAS, Rosa currently resides at the Village de Memoire in Ville Platte; and
17 WHEREAS, reaching the remarkable milestone of one hundred years is a rare and
18 extraordinary achievement, one that reflects a life richly lived and a legacy that will continue
